HEADWORD: Denarius
<hw>De*na"ri*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Denarii</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See 2d
<er>Denier</er>.]</ety> <def>A Roman silver coin of the value of about
fourteen cents; the ⟦ldquo⟧penny⟦rdquo⟧ of the New Testament; -- so
called from being worth originally <xex>ten</xex> of the pieces called
<part>as</part>.</def>⟦br⟧
